Rating: 3
Everyone comments on how light and airy these are. I guess so. They are a mass of leavening. Baking powder, baking soda AND beaten egg whites. So then you use cake flour which leads to a lighter product, too. I'm with the guy who thought that they have too much sugar and I find the vanilla flavor cloying but to each his own. My children liked them and my students loved them. Next time, with all of this leavening power, I'm going with whole wheat flour. Then I'm replacing the sugar and vanilla with two tablespoons of maple syrup in the batter. I'll report back.

