Fabulous! I'm not a huge pumpkin fan, but these sounded so right for Thanksgiving morning, and everyone (including me) loved them! These are the most fluffy, moist pancakes. We reheated a couple of them the next day, and they still tasted great--not too pumpkin tasting, but definitely very holiday tasting. Yum!

Rating: 4
A positive fluke! I made this recipe with great expectations, following carefully the recipe, while at the same time adding a flourish of spice and a great heaping handful of walnuts (perhaps too much at the end of the batch!). At the end I had very very fluffy, extremely light and delicious pancakes! Then, making them again with my sister, I noticed I had completely forgotten the butter the first time I made them! We made them again, still without the butter and they didn't turn out as good. Why? YOU MUST BEAT THE EGG WHITES as directed!! Otherwise they're flat and too dense and don't cook well (Bleh!). I recommend making them without the butter, and with only a small handful of walnuts tossed in the batter. Believe me, you won't notice the absence of butter! They will be light and fluffy and you won't feel as guilty when eating them.

